      "source": [
        "# **Loan Application Status Prediction**\n",
        "\n",
        "Problem Statement:\n",
        "\n",
        "This dataset includes details of applicants who have applied for loan. The dataset\n",
        "includes details like credit history, loan amount, their income, dependents etc.\n",
        "\n",
        "# **Independent Variables:**\n",
        "- Loan_ID\n",
        "- Gender\n",
        "- Married\n",
        "- Dependents\n",
        "- Education\n",
        "- Self_Employed\n",
        "- ApplicantIncome\n",
        "- CoapplicantIncome\n",
        "- Loan_Amount\n",
        "- Loan_Amount_Term\n",
        "- Credit History\n",
        "- Property_Area\n",
        "\n",
        "# **Dependent Variable (Target Variable):**\n",
        "- Loan_Status\n",
        "\n",
        "You have to build a model that can predict whether the loan of the applicant will be\n",
        "approved or not on the basis of the details provided in the dataset"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",

        "#Importing Necessary Libraries\n",
        "import numpy as np #numerical python\n",
        "import pandas as pd #Data manipulation and analysis\n",
        "import sklearn #Machine learning library\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder#encoding\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler#standardizing\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split#spliting the data into training and testing\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression#regression\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier#classification\n",
        "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier#classification\n",
        "from statsmodels.stats.outliers_influence import variance_inflation_factor#checking vif\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, root_mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score#model evaluation metrics\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso, LassoCV, Ridge,  RidgeCV #for linear model cv\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score#cross validation\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV#hyper parameter tunning\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import KFold#cross validation\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, RandomizedSearchCV#for hyperparameter tunning\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve,roc_auc_score#model evaluation\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import RocCurveDisplay#model evaluation\n",
        "import pickle#saving the model\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-ede7fd68-32a5-4f17-9ab0-86f284d9c118');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "      }\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.remove('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",

              "      const buttonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#df-62039d4a-8dec-44f0-977f-64e3aa07a1fe button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "      buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-62039d4a-8dec-44f0-977f-64e3aa07a1fe');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",

              "      }\n",

              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-72bb91de-30e6-4b49-b67b-6b20cef1628d');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",

              "      }\n",

              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-ce51d621-e2fe-48b3-99ce-a4701c165f44');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-85f8c90b-5f7b-496e-9402-3cbcf46ed929');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",

              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-7f82a861-cbcf-4ac7-9231-1a1d874ad1c5');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-1b758647-39d7-490b-bb58-d564b25b2511');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-4d007dd9-5304-48f7-b439-4ede5f94dd6d');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-4543bc74-324d-4284-8af8-55101559d9c8');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "      }\n",

              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-6ee65190-b39f-41a2-a27d-226972d3d384');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

              "    async function quickchart(key) {\n",
              "      const quickchartButtonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#' + key + ' button');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.disabled = true;  // To prevent multiple clicks.\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      try {\n",
              "        const charts = await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction(\n",
              "            'suggestCharts', [key], {});\n",
              "      } catch (error) {\n",
              "        console.error('Error during call to suggestCharts:', error);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.remove('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",
              "    }\n",
              "    (() => {\n",
              "      let quickchartButtonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#df-d3d8af93-fbb6-40dd-860e-74c232191aa9 button');\n",

      "source": [
        "It is used to detect multicollinearity. Multicollinearity occurs when two or more independent variables are highly correlated."
      ]

              "                                                    [key], {});\n",

              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",

        "# **LOAD MODELS**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "m_mJ_XeNWHdf"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "#choose models\n",
        "\n",
        "def model_predict(model, name):\n",
        "\n",
        "    model.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "    train_score = model.score(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "    test_score = model.score(x_test, y_test)\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print('Model: ', name)\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print(f'\\n--Train_Score-->{train_score*100:.2f}%')\n",
        "    print(f'--Test_Score-->{test_score*100:.2f}%')\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "\n",
        "    print('Model Evaluation')\n",
        "    y_pred = model.predict(x_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "    rmse = root_mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "    r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "    print(f'\\n--MSE:--->{mse:.2f}')\n",
        "    print(f'--RMSE:--->{rmse:.2f}')\n",
        "    print(f'--MAE:--->{mae:.2f}')\n",
        "    print(f'--R-squared:--->{r2:.2f}\\n')\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.scatter(y_test,y_pred,color='blue',facecolor='red')\n",
        "    plt.plot(y_test,y_test)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel('Actual Data')\n",
        "    plt.ylabel('Predicted Data')\n",
        "    plt.title(name)\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "# to check if the models are overfitting or not\n",
        "\n",
        "def overfit_check(model_check_overfit, reg_model, reg_model_name):\n",
        "    model_check_overfit.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "    alpha = model_check_overfit.alpha_\n",
        "    reg_model_check = reg_model(alpha, random_state=200)\n",
        "    reg_model_check.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "    reg_score = reg_model_check.score(x_test, y_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print(reg_model_name)\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print('Alpha:--->', alpha)\n",
        "    print('Score:--->', reg_score)"
      ]
    },
    {

      "metadata": {
        "id": "vy_kbp0IhJUn"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def cross_validation(k_folds, model, model_name,  x, y):\n",
        "    kf_cv = KFold(n_splits= k_folds, shuffle=True, random_state=200)\n",
        "    cross_val_results = cross_val_score(model, x, y, cv=kf_cv)\n",
        "\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print(model_name)\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print('Cross_Validation:')\n",
        "    print('-'*30)\n",
        "    # print(f'Cross-Validation Results (Accuracy): {cross_val_results}')\n",
        "    print(f'Mean Accuracy: {cross_val_results.mean()*100:.2f}')"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {

      "metadata": {
        "id": "2fhL2iyJmptq"
      },
      "source": [
        "# **HYPER PARAMETER TUNING**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gJ01HbUlmd0e"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "#Doing hyperparameter tuning on these models"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XID26QSapTR-"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def hyperparameters_tuning(regressor_model, model_name):\n",
        "\n",
        "    if regressor_model == RandomForestClassifier():\n",
        "        grid_param = {\n",
        "            'n_estimators': [50,100,150],\n",
        "            'max_depth': [None, 10, 20],\n",
        "            'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10],\n",
        "            'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4],\n",
        "            'criterion': ['gini', 'log_loss', 'entropy'],  # Changed the criterion values\n",
        "            'max_features': ['sqrt', 'log2', None]\n",
        "        }\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "\n",
        "        grid_param = {\n",
        "            'max_depth': [10, 20, 30, None],\n",
        "            'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10],\n",
        "            'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 4],\n",
        "            'criterion': ['gini', 'log_loss', 'entropy'], # Changed the criterion values\n",
        "            'max_features':['sqrt', 'log2']\n",
        "        }\n",
        "\n",
        "    random_search = RandomizedSearchCV(estimator=regressor_model, param_distributions=grid_param, n_iter=100, cv=5)\n",
        "    random_search.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "    best_model = random_search.best_estimator_\n",
        "    y_pred = best_model.predict(x_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_score = best_model.score(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "    test_score = best_model.score(x_test, y_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    pred_r2_score = r2_score(y_true=y_test, y_pred=y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print('Hyperparameters Tuning Results')\n",
        "    print('='*30)\n",
        "    print(model_name)\n",
        "    print('-'*30)\n",
        "    print(f'Best Hyperparameters:--->{random_search.best_params_}')\n",
        "    print(f'Best Score:--->{random_search.best_score_}/n')\n",
        "    print(f'Train Score:--->{train_score*100}')\n",
        "    print(f'Test Score:--->{test_score*100}')\n",
        "    print(f'Pred_R2_Score:--->{pred_r2_score*100}')\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.scatter(y_test, y_pred, c='b', marker='o', edgecolors='k', alpha=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.plot(y_test,y_test)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel('Actual')\n",
        "    plt.ylabel('Predicted')\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "    return best_model"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "background_save": true,
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix,accuracy_score,classification_report\n",
        "\n",
        "def metrics_score(RFC,X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test,train=True):\n",
        "    if train:\n",
        "        y_pred=RFC.predict(X_train)\n",
        "        print(\"==================Training Score=================\")\n",
        "        print(\"Accuracy Score == >  \", accuracy_score(y_train,y_pred)*100)\n",
        "    elif train==False:\n",
        "        pred=RFC.predict(X_test)\n",
        "        print(\"=================Test Score======================\")\n",
        "        print(\"Accuracy Score==>  \",accuracy_score(y_test,pred)*100)\n",
        "        print(\"Classification Report\",classification_report(y_test,pred))\n",
        "#checking train and test score"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
